Online Savings FAQs







  Is there a minimum deposit amount to open an Online Savings Account? 
		



No, there is no minimum deposit required to open an Online Savings Account. If you fail to fund your Account within 60 days of Account opening, GS Bank may consider your Account closed.







 How do I fund my Online Savings Account or make deposits?
		



There are four ways you can add money to your Account:

Transfer funds between your GS Bank Accounts and external bank accounts that have been linked in Online Banking.
You can direct deposit payments, for example all or part of your payroll or Social Security benefits, directly into your GS Bank Online Savings Account. For payroll, simply provide your employer with the GS Bank routing number (1240-8526-0) and your Account number to enable your employer to deposit funds directly into your Account. For Social Security benefits, you can go to the Social Security Administration website to schedule your direct deposit.
Send a domestic wire transfer Routing Transit Number, wire transfer address and your Account number.


Routing Transit Number (RTN):
1240-8526-0
Wire Transfer Address:
Goldman Sachs Bank USA
 
200 West Street
 
New York, NY 10282


Send a check by U.S. mail (please don't send cash).
Goldman Sachs Bank USA
PO Box 4571
Carol Stream, IL 60197-4571
Please make the check payable to your name (make sure the name is the same as on the account) or Goldman Sachs Bank USA. Please endorse the back of any check with the words “For Deposit Only” and include your Account number.








  How can I access and manage my Account? 
		



Sign In to Online Banking to access and manage your Account online.
In Online Banking, you can:

Check balances
Track your recent transactions and deposits
Choose environmentally-friendly paperless statements to get your statements sooner
Transfer money online securely
Download your 1099-INT tax form
Manage your account profile and preferences, including mailing address, email address, password and more.

You have the option to register for Online Banking at the time you open your first GS Bank Account. If you did not register for Online Banking at the time of Account opening, simply register for access now.








  What fees are associated with my Online Savings Account? 
		



There are no transaction fees at GS Bank.







  How can I withdraw money? 
		





There are two ways you can withdraw money from your Online Savings Account through GS Bank:

Electronic Transfer: Transfer funds to domestic accounts you own at another financial institution that have been linked to your GS Bank Account and that we have verified are owned by you. You can also initiate an electronic transfer from another financial institution.
Wire Transfer: Send a domestic wire transfer to accounts you own at other financial institutions by calling us toll free at 1-855-730-SAVE (7283) Monday through Friday, 7am to 11pm CT. Wires requested after 3pm CT will be considered received on the next business day. In most circumstances, we will only allow a transfer of funds from your Account at GS Bank to an account you own at another financial institution. It may take one (1) to three (3) business days to process your request. Wire transfers are subject to our wire transfer security procedures. You will need to provide the GS Bank Routing Transit Number, the wire transfer address and your Account number.

Routing Transit Number (RTN):    1240-8526-0
Wire Transfer Address:                 Goldman Sachs Bank USA
200 West Street
New York, NY 10282
There is a limit of six withdrawals or transfers in a monthly statement period for Online Savings Accounts.
Note: There is an outgoing transfer limit of $125,000 per transfer when the transfer is initiated online. If you need to withdraw more than $125,000, please call us toll free at 1-855-730-SAVE (7283) Monday through Friday, 7am to 11pm CT.










  How many withdrawals can I make each month? 
		



There is a limit of six withdrawals or transfers in a monthly statement period for Online Savings Accounts.







  What are my online transfer limits? 
		



There is an outgoing transfer limit of $125,000 per transfer when the transfer is initiated online. If you need to withdraw more than $125,000, please call us toll free at 1-855-730-SAVE (7283) Monday through Friday, 7am to 11pm CT.
Note: We may change our transfer limit policies at any time without prior notice, unless required by law.







 How much money can I deposit?
		




